/* 8. Centuries to Minutes

Write a program that receives a number of centuries and converts it to years, days, hours, and minutes.

Examples
Input Output

1 1 centuries = 100 years = 36524 days = 876576 hours = 52594560 minutes
5 5 centuries = 500 years = 182621 days = 4382904 hours = 262974240 minutes

Hint Â· Assume that a year has 365.2422 days on average (the Tropical year).  */


function centuriesConverted(centuryNumber){

    let numberOfCenturies = centuryNumber;
    let numberOfYears = centuryNumber * 100;
    let numberOfDays = Math.floor(numberOfYears * 365.2422);
    let numberOfHours = numberOfDays * 24;
    let numberOfMinutes = numberOfHours * 60;
   
    console.log(`${numberOfCenturies} centuries = ${numberOfYears} years = ${numberOfDays} days = ${numberOfHours} hours = ${numberOfMinutes} minutes`);
}


centuriesConverted(1);
centuriesConverted(5);
